text.tspan: Share of adult women overweight or obese vs. daily caloric supply, 1975 to
The share of adult women defined as overweight or obese, measured as the percentage of women with a body mass index
(BMI) greater than 25.0, versus the daily caloric supply, measured in kilocalories per person per day. Body Mass Index (BMI)
is a person's weight in kilograms (kg) divided by his or her height (in meters), squared (m2). The WHO define a BMI >25.0
Share of women overweight or obese
Source: FAO (2017) & Various historical sources, Prevalence of weight categories in females - NCDRisC (2017), Population (Gapminder,
